You can modify your existing rules to restrict write access to the "posts" node to only the authenticated "admin" user. Here's how you can do that:

```
{
  "rules": {
    "posts": {
      ".read": true,
      ".write": "root.child('users').child(auth.uid).child('admin').val() === true"
    },
    "users": {
      "$uid": {
        ".read": "$uid === auth.uid",
        ".write": "$uid === auth.uid"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

In the above code, we've added a new rule for the "posts" node. Here are what the rules mean:

- `.read` - allows anyone to read the posts node
- `.write` - restricts write access to only the authenticated user with an "admin" field value of true in their user data

Note: You will need to make sure that your "admin" field is set to true for the user you want to give write access to the "posts" node, and set to false for all other users.

